  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Mila 18 headquarter was quite well prepared for-- with many things, including some food, to resist for some period of time, until there was a-- this what people see today with the monument to the bunker was a very nice building standing with all facilities intact, prepared for absorption of people.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was all shattered to pieces by the German artillery and-- and the air force.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were using air force to-- to devastate the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My main thing was to-- at night to prepare Molotov cocktails out of any little cans or-- or bottles, and to gather the material for it, and show the other people how to prepare it.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the other thing was delivering messages from bunker to bunker.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Very simply.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You-- you had a wick.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the wick we prepared out of cotton mixed with-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I'm losing my word.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I am-- the wick was mixed with threads of-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] how do you call this?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Plumbers are using this for-- palm-- palm string.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And also using-- using burlap up and twisting it into thread until it became really soakable.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Then we just left a little bit out of it with-- at the opening of the bottle, we placed [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] paraffin-- paraffin is substance of use for candles-- and very gently opening it, so the gasoline can be soaked up and be affected by the-- by the heat of the wick.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You had to make your choice of the proper material for this, since it was of great importance that a wick will be ignited at the time when it hits and explodes, that the wick is lit and stays lit with a little bit of soaking that penetrates from the bottle.",
      "word_count": 51
    }
  ],
